{{!-- Description
###
Skill takes a JSON object as input and converts it into a plain-text representation where each key-value pair is displayed on a new line in the format:
key: value

Input:
A JSON object, which may contain key-value pairs where keys are strings and values can be strings, numbers, or other primitives.

Output:
A string where each line represents a key-value pair from the JSON, formatted as:
key: value

Recommended Usage: It is highly recommended to use JSON objects with only one level of depth, i.e., no nested objects or arrays, for best results. Nested objects may not be handled or displayed properly.
If a nested object or array is encountered, its representation may not align with the expected output format.

Example:
For the input JSON:
{
    "average_bill_per_person": "50",
    "call_center_savings": "0"
}

The output string would be:
average_bill_per_person: 50
call_center_savings: 0

### --}}

{{Set(name="formatted_object", value=jsonObject.replace('{', " "))}}
{{Set(name="formatted_object", value=formatted_object.replace('}', " "))}}
{{Set(name="formatted_object", value=formatted_object.replace('"', " "))}}
{{Set(name="formatted_object", value=formatted_object.replace(",", "
"))}}
{{Set(name="formatted_object", value=formatted_object.replace(" : ", ": "))}}

{{Return(val=formatted_object)}}
